comments: Quinones (GSW) releases his pass and does not stop and establish legal screening position, rather, Quinones seeks out Hendricks (UTA) and delivers contact that displaces the defender as he moves to defend the ball.
Yurtseven (UTA) is in the paint for longer than three seconds.
Sensabaugh (UTA) leaves both his feet and releases the ball in the air to start his dribble. Possession is properly awarded to Golden State.
Hendricks (UTA) moves laterally into Robinson's (GSW) path and the body contact after Robinson's gather alters his driving shot attempt in the paint.
Yurtseven (UTA) firms up over his left leg and marginal contact occurs with Robinson (GSW) as he maneuvers under the pick.
Yurtseven (UTA) raises his right arm towards the ball and marginal contact occurs with Garuba's (GSW) arm as he secures the rebound.
Yurtseven (UTA) moves alongside Garuba's (GSW) path and marginal contact occurs during Garuba's layup attempt in the paint.
Spencer (GSW) and Yurtseven (UTA) come together in the air while pursuing the loose ball and the contact is marginal.
Yurtseven (UTA) rests his hand on Spencer's (GSW) side and he removes the marginal contact as Spencer elevates for the shot attempt in the paint.
Garuba (GSW) cleanly blocks Yurtseven's (UTA) shot attempt in front of the basket.

Hendricks (UTA) brings his left hand towards the ball and brushes it, which dislodges it away from Quinones (GSW) during his dribble. After the contact with the ball, Hendricks' arm continues sweeping to his right and incidental contact occurs with Quinones' arm.
Hendricks (UTA) dislodges the ball into the backcourt and Quinones (GSW) goes into the backcourt and legally recovers the loose ball and reestablishes it in the frontcourt.

Garuba (GSW) brings his left hand toward the ball and marginal brush contact occurs with the side of Yurtseven's (UTA) head/face. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
